==English==

===Etymology===
From French [[toxicologie]] < Greek [[τοξικόν]] (arrow poison) < [[τοξικός]] (pertaining to archery) + [[λόγος]] (principle).

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''toxicology'''

# the branch of [[pharmacology]] that deals with the [[nature]], [[effect]], [[detection]] and [[treatment]] of [[poison]]s and [[poisoning]]

